I feel so relaxed.

01:32.880 --> 01:35.155
You know the help is off, Crewe.

01:35.360 --> 01:37.191
The phones are off.

01:38.280 --> 01:39.872
We're all alone.

01:42.240 --> 01:45.630
Let's get it on, honey. Come on.

01:46.680 --> 01:49.752
- Honey.
- What?

01:49.960 --> 01:54.112
Wake up, baby. Come on.
You know it'll be good.

01:54.320 --> 01:57.869
You know how good it is.
Come on, Crewe.

01:58.080 --> 01:59.911
Get off me!

02:02.160 --> 02:04.799
Son of a bitch.

02:13.240 --> 02:14.832
Where are you going?

02:15.760 --> 02:18.957
- Splitting.
- Splitting?

02:19.160 --> 02:23.950
You split when I tell you to split,
you All-American son of a bitch.

02:24.160 --> 02:25.991
Lovely, lovely.

02:29.440 --> 02:32.113
And when you walk out, stay out.

02:32.320 --> 02:34.595
You're too expensive to be useless.

02:39.720 --> 02:40.994
Whore!

02:42.040 --> 02:48.434
- That's exactly what you are, a whore.
- I never looked at it that way before.

02:48.640 --> 02:50.517
Everybody's bought you.

02:50.720 --> 02:54.030
Colleges, the pros, your gamblers.

02:54.240 --> 02:56.470
Who bought those
beautiful caps on your teeth,

02:56.680 --> 02:59.399
the clothes you're wearing
and the bloody tan you've got?

02:59.600 --> 03:01.033
Me!

03:02.280 --> 03:05.431
Have I ever neglected to thank you,
Melissa?

03:05.640 --> 03:07.278
You has-been.

03:07.760 --> 03:09.034
Where're your keys?

03:09.240 --> 03:13.119
If I took everything back... Forget
my keys! You'd be bare-assed naked.

03:13.320 --> 03:17.233
- Where're your goddamn keys?
- Don't touch my keys.

03:20.160 --> 03:22.993
I think the love
has gone out of our relationship.

03:23.200 --> 03:24.633
Bastard.

03:26.600 --> 03:29.034
Don't you take my Masseratti.

03:29.240 --> 03:31.470
I earned it.

03:35.640 --> 03:39.428
I told you not to touch
my goddamn car!

04:13.960 --> 04:15.234
Police.

07:00.920 --> 07:06.358
- Do you have a driver's licence?
- What, are you taking a poll?

07:08.480 --> 07:11.950
Well, look what we got here.
A miniature cop.

07:14.840 --> 07:16.512
Can we see your driver's licence?

07:17.360 --> 07:18.634
What?

07:18.840 --> 07:21.149
Can we see your driver's licence?

07:21.360 --> 07:24.432
See if I can get it out.

07:29.520 --> 07:30.919
It's him all right.

07:31.120 --> 07:33.076
Why'd you dump her car in the Bay?

07:33.280 --> 07:36.078
- What?
- Why'd you dump her car in the Bay?

07:36.280 --> 07:38.840
I couldn't find a car wash.

07:47.840 --> 07:49.398
Step away from the bar.

07:51.240 --> 07:53.834
Mister, step away from the bar!

07:54.040 --> 07:56.793
Don't get pushy, cowboy.

08:00.960 --> 08:03.554
- Turn it around.
- Come on!

08:10.400 --> 08:13.233
- Hold that son of a bitch!
- Damn!

08:13.440 --> 08:17.319
Now we got you
for stealing a car, drunken driving,

08:17.520 --> 08:20.159
drunk in public and resisting arrest.

08:22.400 --> 08:26.871
- Want something else?
- Yeah. I'm going to make you taller.

09:12.160 --> 09:14.037
OK, men, let's go.

09:38.040 --> 09:39.996
Good afternoon.
Where are you from?

09:40.200 --> 09:43.749
- Palm Beach County.
- Thank you, sir. Second door down.

09:44.360 --> 09:45.634
This way, men.

09:45.840 --> 09:49.628
They gave you $10,000
for shaving off your moustache on TV?

09:52.600 --> 09:55.068
How about giving me $5,000 worth?

09:56.840 --> 10:02.198
Coming right off: There's about
twenty-five hundred, three thousand,

10:02.400 --> 10:04.038
four thousand coming up,

10:04.240 --> 10:06.515
five thousand!

10:17.400 --> 10:19.960
- Anything else, sir?
- That's it.

11:03.000 --> 11:05.719
Warden Hazen thinks
you're pretty hot stuff.

11:06.880 --> 11:09.348
But I'm Captain Knauer.

11:09.560 --> 11:13.792
I'm going to spell
things out for you. I run this prison.

11:14.440 --> 11:17.193
He sits there growing old.
I'm out here busting heads.

11:18.080 --> 11:19.991
And I run the football team.

11:20.440 --> 11:23.113
- What football team?
- My football team.

11:24.000 --> 11:25.274
Oh.

11:26.080 --> 11:28.913
Now, Hazen's going to ask you
to help coach.

11:29.120 --> 11:31.634
And you just tell him, "No way".

11:39.560 --> 11:40.879
Know something?

11:44.840 --> 11:46.831
I don't like you.

11:48.280 --> 11:50.555
You understand that?

11:50.760 --> 11:52.591
Oh, yeah.

11:55.040 --> 11:59.716
<i>Attention Cell Block 3 A. Please report
as scheduled to your period assignment,</i>

11:59.920 --> 12:02.229
<i>except for carpentry
and accounting classes.</i>

12:02.440 --> 12:07.798
<i>All men assigned to farm detail will
meet at one o'clock in the Rotunda.</i>

12:09.840 --> 12:13.037
Warden, Captain Knauer's here
with inmate Crewe.

12:13.760 --> 12:16.911
<i>- Send him in.
- Thank you, sir.</i>

12:18.320 --> 12:22.279
- You can go in now.
- Thank you, Miss Toot.

12:36.600 --> 12:38.397
Paul Crewe.

12:39.680 --> 12:41.511
The Wrecking Crewe.

12:44.720 --> 12:47.792
- It's good to have you here.
- Thank you.

12:51.160 --> 12:55.073
Young people can learn a great deal
from a skilful football game.

12:55.280 --> 12:59.751
Offence, defence,
spirit of achievement, teamwork.

13:04.680 --> 13:06.796
You might say...

13:12.080 --> 13:16.039
...the game embodies
what has made our country great.

13:17.040 --> 13:20.191
It's a great game.
It's played by great men.

13:23.320 --> 13:29.555
We have something of a football team
here ourselves, you know.

13:31.200 --> 13:34.636
First rank, semi-pro,
South-eastern League.

13:34.840 --> 13:38.150
Runner-up, National Champions,
past five years.

13:39.520 --> 13:43.308
Mister Crewe,
what do you think of semi-pro ball?

13:43.520 --> 13:45.556
Semi-pro's a joke.

13:49.640 --> 13:55.715
Well, perhaps we could use
a few pointers from the big leagues.

13:55.920 --> 14:00.596
Captain, what do you say
to Mister Crewe here looking in,

14:00.800 --> 14:03.678
giving us the benefit
of his invaluable knowledge?

14:04.200 --> 14:09.399
That's a real good idea, Warden.
We could use all the help we can get.

14:10.280 --> 14:11.952
Well?

14:12.160 --> 14:16.199
I haven't held a football in eight
years. I'm not in very good shape.

14:16.400 --> 14:19.153
Nobody's asked you to play,
Mister Crewe.

14:19.360 --> 14:23.956
What we need is a coach. New blood.

14:24.160 --> 14:25.878
New game plan.

14:30.720 --> 14:35.475
Anybody who was pro football's
Most Valuable Player is special,

14:35.680 --> 14:38.319
and I want to have that.

14:40.120 --> 14:42.031
I'm not interested in football anymore.

14:45.920 --> 14:49.993
Mister Crewe, I don't mind saying,

14:50.760 --> 14:53.228
I pulled a lot of strings
to get you down here.

14:54.240 --> 14:55.673
I appreciate that.

14:56.240 --> 14:58.151
Look.

14:58.360 --> 15:01.477
What I want is a national title.

15:02.800 --> 15:06.679
If, perchance, you should help us
achieve that goal,

15:06.880 --> 15:11.556
I expect your stay here
with us will be very agreeable.

15:13.000 --> 15:14.274
Well?

15:18.200 --> 15:22.159
I just want to do my time,
then get out of here.

15:23.160 --> 15:24.593
Very well.

15:30.760 --> 15:35.550
All right, I'll turn you over
to the good hands of Captain Knauer.

15:35.760 --> 15:37.352
Swamp reclamation.

15:39.120 --> 15:41.839
Get him out of here.

15:45.600 --> 15:47.830
- Captain.
- Yes, sir.

15:48.040 --> 15:49.837
I'd like a word with you.

15:52.480 --> 15:57.315
For the past five years,
you've promised me the national title,

15:57.520 --> 15:59.795
<i>and every year,
you've come up short.</i>

16:00.000 --> 16:03.470
<i>- I try, sir.
- When I want an answer, I'll indicate.</i>

16:03.680 --> 16:05.477
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

16:05.680 --> 16:07.352
<i>You've asked for bonus money.</i>

16:07.560 --> 16:10.313
Certainly take their football
seriously, don't they?

16:10.760 --> 16:14.753
<i>This year you've asked for new
game uniforms. I've OK'ed them.</i>

16:15.400 --> 16:17.391
Everything you've asked for,
I've given you.

16:17.600 --> 16:20.319
Yes, sir. And I appreciate it, sir.

16:21.760 --> 16:24.149
I want that title.

16:24.360 --> 16:27.591
You'll give me that title,
or you'll be out of a job.

16:27.800 --> 16:31.156
You and all that
over-priced beef you call a team.

16:31.360 --> 16:34.033
We should be
in the Superbowl by now!

16:34.880 --> 16:38.873
<i>I've lost patience! The gravy train is
over! This year you're going to win!</i>

16:39.080 --> 16:40.399
You've lovely hair.

16:40.600 --> 16:45.435
<i>...your last chance! Prison is no
different from any other community.</i>

16:46.200 --> 16:49.112
Ever find any spiders in it?

16:49.320 --> 16:51.231
<i>...then I haven't done my job.</i>

16:51.720 --> 16:53.790
I'm not being unreasonable, am I?

16:54.680 --> 16:57.240
- No, sir.
- Then you'll give me the title?

16:57.440 --> 16:59.795
- Yes, sir.
- Good!

17:01.280 --> 17:03.669
I want that man out there.

17:03.880 --> 17:08.749
And I want you to make
that son of a bitch enthusiastic!

17:10.839 --> 17:14.469
- Ever do it standing up?
- Let's move it.

17:22.480 --> 17:26.108
- I say forget football, you do it.
- Why are you so mad?

17:26.319 --> 17:31.952
- You better start taking life seriously.
- I did exactly what you told me to do.

17:51.280 --> 17:53.794
Hey, Superstar.
Get a good night's sleep?

17:54.000 --> 17:56.150
Too bad you missed breakfast.
It was yummy!

17:57.240 --> 17:58.673
Gotta get it done.

17:58.880 --> 18:03.795
- This is make-work day.
- What's make-work day?

18:04.000 --> 18:06.230
You shovel it in
and shovel back out again.

18:06.440 --> 18:09.557
Hustle in there now.
Cover that bank.

18:09.760 --> 18:12.115
Get that wheelbarrow, Woody.

18:12.920 --> 18:14.638
Let's go. Single file.

18:14.840 --> 18:18.628
Hang it up, hang it up.
Let's get covered.

18:20.240 --> 18:23.437
All right, let's go. Come on.

18:23.640 --> 18:25.471
Get a shovel.

18:28.160 --> 18:29.559
Hey, Superstar.

18:32.120 --> 18:34.998
I got an idea. Granny.

18:41.120 --> 18:44.112
You ever work with a nigger before?

18:47.520 --> 18:49.272
Get another shovel there, boy.

18:55.880 --> 18:58.394
All right. Let's go.

19:04.080 --> 19:05.911
Heave it up!

19:07.280 --> 19:10.955
- Sitting down, boss?
- Not today, boy.

19:16.600 --> 19:20.673
- Wiping off, boss?
- Not today, boy.

19:22.360 --> 19:25.079
- Rolling one, boss?
- Not yet, boy.

19:26.280 --> 19:29.192
Now you know
how black man's work feels.

19:29.400 --> 19:30.879
How do you like it?

19:31.080 --> 19:33.230
Oh, it sort of grows on you.

19:33.440 --> 19:34.998
No talking there, Granny.

19:35.720 --> 19:40.157
- Yes, boss.
- You'll find yourselves in bad time.

19:40.360 --> 19:44.194
Yes, boss. Sorry about that, boss.

19:44.640 --> 19:47.279
What's he think this is, good time?

19:47.480 --> 19:51.837
Looky, looky, looky,
here comes cooky!

19:58.880 --> 20:03.510
Big deal. Look at him now.

20:06.200 --> 20:09.317
How do you like them apples,
Superstar?

20:12.960 --> 20:14.439
Move the line.

20:59.000 --> 21:00.956
Real friendly types
you got around here.

21:01.160 --> 21:04.869
- Might be your own fault.
- Oh, really?

21:05.080 --> 21:08.914
Most of these old boys have nothing.
Never had nothing to start with.

21:09.120 --> 21:12.749
But you, you had it all.

21:12.960 --> 21:16.396
Then you let your team-mates down,
got caught taking bribes.

21:17.200 --> 21:20.158
- I did, did I?
- I ain't saying either way.

21:20.360 --> 21:22.920
I'm just saying
you could've robbed banks, sold dope,

21:23.120 --> 21:26.635
stole your grandmother's pension,
and none of us would've minded.

21:26.840 --> 21:31.356
But shaving points off a football game,
that's un-American.

21:34.560 --> 21:36.551
You take football
real serious down here.

21:37.520 --> 21:40.796
- Mind if I ask you one question?
- Yeah, I do.

21:41.000 --> 21:42.991
Why'd you do it?

21:43.200 --> 21:47.876
- It's a long story.
- Well, I got eight years.

21:58.840 --> 22:02.150
Oh, my God.
What the hell is that?

22:02.360 --> 22:06.114
That's a member
of the warden's football team.

22:06.320 --> 22:10.074
Some of these guards are not
just everyday run-of-the-mill guards.

22:13.240 --> 22:16.437
Crewe! Granville! Front and centre.

22:16.640 --> 22:18.710
What now?

22:18.920 --> 22:23.232
That means we don't get
to finish this delicious lunch.

22:34.200 --> 22:35.553
What's he looking for?

22:36.840 --> 22:38.319
Snakes.

22:38.520 --> 22:40.795
- Snakes?
- Yeah.

22:49.720 --> 22:51.915
Take five!

23:00.720 --> 23:04.599
- Rolling one, boss?
- Not today, boy.

23:10.760 --> 23:12.159
Jeez!

23:25.640 --> 23:28.757
- Terrific.
- Football faggot!

23:31.720 --> 23:35.076
- Salt pill up here, boss?
- Go get it, boy.

23:35.880 --> 23:37.996
How long you been in this asylum,
Pop?

23:38.200 --> 23:39.792
Thirty-four years.

23:40.000 --> 23:42.116
- Thirty-four years?
- Yep.

23:42.320 --> 23:45.437
Last six and a half
right here in the swamp.

23:45.640 --> 23:49.030
Too old for reclamation,
so they made me barracks chief.

23:49.920 --> 23:52.673
Aren't you coming up
for parole soon?

23:52.880 --> 23:59.035
Thirty years ago, I made the mistake
of slugging a fish bull. Hazen.

24:00.120 --> 24:02.918
Just my luck he made warden.

24:03.120 --> 24:09.195
Sent me out here when I was 64 to die,
but I've been hanging on.

24:09.400 --> 24:14.110
We'll all be in the same place a thousand
years from now, so what the hell.

24:14.320 --> 24:17.551
Yeah. What the hell.

24:19.960 --> 24:23.794
All right, you assholes.
Back to work.

24:26.960 --> 24:28.757
Hey!

24:30.240 --> 24:33.994
This ain't no country club, Superstar.
Move your ass.

24:40.720 --> 24:44.508
No, no, son.
You've got to get off the bunk.

24:44.720 --> 24:47.632
Man, for God's sake, get up.

24:49.200 --> 24:50.838
On your feet.

24:51.040 --> 24:57.070
Listen to me. Nobody's allowed on the
bunks till five minutes before lights out.

24:58.920 --> 25:01.753
They'll put you in the oven.

25:03.000 --> 25:05.389
Man, that can kill you.

25:07.360 --> 25:10.079
Did you have any supper yet?

25:10.280 --> 25:11.713
No.

25:11.920 --> 25:14.150
Later I'll try to get you some chow.

25:14.360 --> 25:17.750
You got to eat, man,
or you'll die of mono.

25:18.360 --> 25:20.874
And they could care less.

25:29.560 --> 25:31.835
- Get off me!
- Hey, watch it, man!

25:32.040 --> 25:33.837
Where the hell you going?

25:35.240 --> 25:38.630
Twinkle, twinkle, little Superstar.

25:43.960 --> 25:45.552
- Guard.
- Yeah?

25:45.760 --> 25:49.355
I want to see the warden.

26:01.640 --> 26:03.073
Pass the salt.

26:49.640 --> 26:51.517
Boy.

28:18.160 --> 28:19.434
Come on.

28:42.960 --> 28:44.791
Go, baby!

29:25.880 --> 29:30.078
That's going to get you
twenty-four hours in the hot box, boy.

29:31.920 --> 29:34.070
I quit.

29:43.040 --> 29:44.871
What makes you so tough?

29:45.600 --> 29:48.398
I don't know. It just comes natural.

29:49.760 --> 29:51.990
That'll cost you, boy.

30:11.120 --> 30:12.838
Rise and shine.

30:13.320 --> 30:15.038
Rise and shine.

30:21.400 --> 30:24.597
Oh. It's room service.

30:24.800 --> 30:26.677
Pretty gamey.

30:29.400 --> 30:33.439
Shower and put on some clean whites.
The warden wants to see you.

30:33.640 --> 30:37.110
- The warden?
- Get on down there.

30:51.160 --> 30:52.718
Well?

30:53.360 --> 30:56.557
- What do you think of my team?
- Mean.

30:57.120 --> 30:58.997
Crude, but mean.

30:59.520 --> 31:03.433
I was depending on you, you know.

31:03.640 --> 31:08.794
Well, there's so little time left now,
it's quite a problem.

31:09.760 --> 31:13.196
They need something
before that first game.

31:15.520 --> 31:18.557
- You have to win the first game?
- Right.

31:18.760 --> 31:20.637
Well, it's relatively simple.

31:20.840 --> 31:24.594
Yeah. Get yourself a tune-up game,
you know?

31:24.800 --> 31:26.791
A what?

31:27.000 --> 31:32.279
A tune-up game, like the pros have,
with a hungry team not in your league.

31:32.480 --> 31:35.313
You bring them here
and kick the shit out of them.

31:36.240 --> 31:37.514
Well.

31:39.800 --> 31:43.588
How do you think
we'd do against the pros?

31:43.800 --> 31:46.234
- That team against the pros?
- Yeah.

31:46.440 --> 31:49.591
You'd have a real problem.

31:49.800 --> 31:54.828
Well, how do you think
we'd do against the cons?

31:56.200 --> 31:58.395
- I didn't know they had a team.
- They don't.

31:59.520 --> 32:02.512
But you've given me an inspiration.

32:02.720 --> 32:06.838
I've decided, Mister Crewe, that
you're going to put one together for me.

32:07.040 --> 32:10.191
