Ready? Break.

01:36:51.040 --> 01:36:54.919
OK. Come on.
Looks good. Keep it alive.

01:36:57.120 --> 01:36:58.599
Set!

01:37:00.920 --> 01:37:02.638
Hut!

01:37:09.760 --> 01:37:12.274
<i>There's a first down
on the 20-yard line.</i>

01:37:15.520 --> 01:37:16.794
Your confidence back?

01:37:17.720 --> 01:37:20.359
- Get Scarboro.
- Son of a bitch.

01:37:23.480 --> 01:37:27.758
<i>Ball goes back to Crewe,
he's waiting to pass...</i>

01:37:40.040 --> 01:37:44.238
<i>...by Bogdanski. Bogdanski hit
Nate Scarboro a cheap shot.</i>

01:37:44.440 --> 01:37:46.396
<i>A reprehensible action.</i>

01:37:47.000 --> 01:37:48.752
Cheap shot!

01:37:51.240 --> 01:37:53.117
Let me at the son of a bitch.

01:37:55.560 --> 01:37:58.870
Old Double O
is down and seems badly hurt.

01:37:59.880 --> 01:38:01.757
How is it, Nate?

01:38:01.960 --> 01:38:06.670
I love it. After all these years,
my first touchdown.

01:38:07.480 --> 01:38:10.119
It's got to be his knee.
I heard it pop.

01:38:11.160 --> 01:38:13.879
- Get him up.
- You'll be OK. Hang in there.

01:38:21.280 --> 01:38:23.555
Hey, Paul. You've got to do it.

01:38:25.920 --> 01:38:28.878
- Screw Hazen!
- Don't worry. He'll get his.

01:38:31.080 --> 01:38:32.798
<i>Good old Nate Scarboro.</i>

01:38:33.000 --> 01:38:35.878
One of the most beloved men
this institution has had.

01:38:47.560 --> 01:38:50.632
<i>The extra point kick is good.</i>

01:38:50.840 --> 01:38:53.718
<i>Tightening that score now
to 35 to 20.</i>

01:38:55.160 --> 01:38:59.358
Blue Eyes can kick the ball ten yards,
can someone fall on it?

01:38:59.560 --> 01:39:02.472
- Right on.
- Then let's go!

01:39:08.160 --> 01:39:11.152
<i>Charlie Blue Eyes approaches the ball
and kicks...</i>

01:39:11.360 --> 01:39:13.555
<i>It's an on-side kick...</i>

01:39:19.520 --> 01:39:22.432
<i>And it's recovered
for the Mean Machine.</i>

01:39:25.400 --> 01:39:28.039
Shut up. Shut up!

01:39:28.240 --> 01:39:30.071
You're stinking the place up.

01:39:30.680 --> 01:39:33.717
- Can we take 'em?
- Yeah!

01:39:38.240 --> 01:39:41.232
Split right. On two. Ready?

01:39:49.640 --> 01:39:51.153
Set!

01:39:52.520 --> 01:39:54.078
Hut!

01:39:54.280 --> 01:39:57.875
<i>Ball goes back to Crewe.
Crewe hands off to number 30...</i>

01:40:05.400 --> 01:40:08.153
<i>...23 yards.
Crewe's down on the ten-yard line.</i>

01:40:08.360 --> 01:40:10.032
A beautiful piece of razzle-dazzle.

01:40:10.760 --> 01:40:16.073
<i>Paul Crewe reached into
his bag of tricks that time, folks.</i>

01:40:29.440 --> 01:40:33.797
<i>Charlie Blue Eyes splits the uprights
and that makes it 35 to 27.</i>

01:40:34.000 --> 01:40:36.719
- How we doing?
- Fine.

01:40:36.920 --> 01:40:39.275
There you go, Nate.

01:40:39.480 --> 01:40:42.950
I heard you were on your way in.

01:40:45.840 --> 01:40:48.832
Hey, did they tell you
about my touchdown?

01:40:49.040 --> 01:40:53.431
<i>We repeat, with five minutes and
four seconds left in the fourth quarter,</i>

01:40:53.640 --> 01:40:56.074
<i>there is now only
an eight-point difference.</i>

01:41:00.720 --> 01:41:03.837
- Here we go.
- Can you drop-kick from here?

01:41:04.040 --> 01:41:06.110
- I could try.
- Drop-kick?

01:41:07.040 --> 01:41:09.110
It's fourth and four
and we're going to drop-kick.

01:41:09.320 --> 01:41:13.029
Shotgun.
Drop-kick, on one. Ready?

01:41:18.080 --> 01:41:20.435
<i>...he's got to come up
with something different.</i>

01:41:22.400 --> 01:41:24.630
<i>Ball goes back to
Charlie Blue Eyes...</i>

01:41:29.760 --> 01:41:31.591
I haven't seen one
of those in years.

01:41:32.480 --> 01:41:35.074
- What was that?
- A drop-kick.

01:41:35.280 --> 01:41:38.511
- How much does that count?
- Three points.

01:41:38.920 --> 01:41:41.957
For that? Bullshit!

01:41:43.760 --> 01:41:46.832
<i>The score stands Guards 35,
Mean Machine 30.</i>

01:41:47.040 --> 01:41:50.316
<i>Fourth and 21
for the Mean Machine on their own 39.</i>

01:41:50.520 --> 01:41:53.034
<i>Crewe is feigning...</i>

01:41:53.240 --> 01:41:55.708
<i>...and he dumps off another pass.</i>

01:42:04.880 --> 01:42:07.269
<i>...Bogdanski saves a touchdown.</i>

01:42:07.480 --> 01:42:10.995
Bogdanski is really wreaking havoc
on that Mean Machine team.

01:42:14.000 --> 01:42:16.434
Quiet down.
Now, listen to me.

01:42:17.120 --> 01:42:20.795
We're going to let Bogdanski come right
through. Nobody touch him. Got it?

01:42:21.000 --> 01:42:25.676
I want to try something.
If it works, everybody hit him. Right?

01:42:25.880 --> 01:42:30.874
- Right.
- Split right. All curl, on one. Ready?

01:42:31.640 --> 01:42:32.914
Red left!

01:42:33.400 --> 01:42:36.039
Blue 69!

01:42:36.480 --> 01:42:38.596
Blue 69!

01:42:40.200 --> 01:42:41.792
Set!

01:42:45.880 --> 01:42:49.111
<i>...throws the ball
directly at Bogdanski's groin.</i>

01:42:53.080 --> 01:42:55.355
- Get off him.
- That's bullshit!

01:42:57.600 --> 01:43:00.114
<i>They're unravelling the tangle now,</i>

01:43:00.320 --> 01:43:03.676
and there's a penalty against
the Mean Machine for roughness,

01:43:03.880 --> 01:43:09.113
<i>and that pass sure didn't look like
it was an accident.</i>

01:43:09.600 --> 01:43:13.878
Bogdanski is staggering,
but he is up and on his feet.

01:43:14.080 --> 01:43:19.552
OK. We've got fifteenth.
Let's huddle up on the ball. Huddle up.

01:43:26.240 --> 01:43:27.514
Unbelievable.

01:43:36.200 --> 01:43:38.031
Hey, Bog.
Get out of here.

01:43:38.240 --> 01:43:40.435
- Come on.
- I know what I'm doing.

01:43:40.640 --> 01:43:44.474
- Worked once, got to work again. Right?
- Right.

01:43:44.680 --> 01:43:48.958
All right.
One more time, on two. Ready?

01:43:49.160 --> 01:43:53.119
<i>It's third and 32
for the Mean Machine.</i>

01:43:59.080 --> 01:44:01.469
Set!
Hut!

01:44:01.680 --> 01:44:03.910
<i>Ball goes back to Crewe...</i>

01:44:05.440 --> 01:44:08.034
Crewe hits Bogdanski with the ball
right in the...

01:44:08.240 --> 01:44:10.629
<i>...in the nether regions.</i>

01:44:10.840 --> 01:44:14.469
<i>Once again, Bogdanski is down,
the Mean Machine is dirty.</i>

01:44:29.480 --> 01:44:32.438
- He's not breathing.
- Do something. Try mouth-to-mouth.

01:44:33.040 --> 01:44:36.794
- You want to?
- No way.

01:44:37.360 --> 01:44:38.679
Ambulance. Help!

01:44:40.520 --> 01:44:45.878
<i>They are taking Bogdanski
off the field in an ambulance.</i>

01:45:09.680 --> 01:45:11.875
He pushed him!

01:45:16.360 --> 01:45:19.636
You can't see,
you blind son of a bitch.

01:45:19.840 --> 01:45:24.118
Hey, Walking Boss,
here's your crying towel.

01:45:24.320 --> 01:45:27.198
You big fat-assed son of a bitch.

01:45:27.400 --> 01:45:30.790
Go get off and stay off.

01:45:31.000 --> 01:45:32.433
First down.

01:45:33.280 --> 01:45:34.554
Time out.

01:45:34.760 --> 01:45:36.352
Jesus!

01:45:38.720 --> 01:45:41.678
- Scooter, you want to hit somebody?
- Yeah.

01:45:41.880 --> 01:45:44.792
All right. Tackle eligible.

01:45:45.000 --> 01:45:46.831
Mawabe, talk to me.

01:45:47.040 --> 01:45:49.508
- What are you doing?
- One step off the line.

01:45:49.720 --> 01:45:51.950
- I'll step on the line.
- Right. On one. Ready?

01:45:52.160 --> 01:45:57.188
Machine's ball, first and ten
on the Guards' 31-yard line.

01:45:57.400 --> 01:45:58.833
Blue 28!

01:45:59.040 --> 01:46:01.952
<i>...less than one minute
57 seconds left.</i>

01:46:02.720 --> 01:46:04.278
Hut!

01:46:11.480 --> 01:46:13.198
Protest that play!

01:46:23.520 --> 01:46:24.953
Crewe, call time.

01:46:25.600 --> 01:46:28.876
Time. Time.
Time, ref. Time.

01:46:29.080 --> 01:46:31.878
<i>First and goal on the one-yard line,</i>

01:46:32.080 --> 01:46:34.036
as Crewe calls time out, with...

01:46:34.240 --> 01:46:37.152
<i>...40 seconds left on the clock.</i>

01:46:37.360 --> 01:46:39.828
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

01:46:40.040 --> 01:46:43.430
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

01:46:43.640 --> 01:46:45.358
Mean Machine!

01:46:47.800 --> 01:46:50.234
Quiet down. Split right...
Joe Jack!

01:46:50.440 --> 01:46:53.273
Split right, sweep left.
On one. Ready?

01:46:55.200 --> 01:46:58.397
Blue 28! Blue 28!

01:46:58.600 --> 01:47:00.352
Set! Hut!

01:47:07.440 --> 01:47:10.034
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
this is really a ball game.</i>

01:47:10.240 --> 01:47:12.276
This is a great ball team.

01:47:12.480 --> 01:47:16.439
<i>They're giving these Guardsmen
the fight of their lives.</i>

01:47:19.800 --> 01:47:23.156
Split right, roll out right,
option pass. Be waiting, Mace.

01:47:23.360 --> 01:47:25.396
On two, on two. Ready?

01:47:25.600 --> 01:47:28.558
<i>- Second and goal.
- Blue 20.</i>

01:47:29.720 --> 01:47:33.429
Blue 20. Set! Hut!

01:47:34.920 --> 01:47:36.399
<i>Crewe feigns the pass...</i>

01:47:37.080 --> 01:47:40.072
<i>...and he throws...</i>

01:47:40.280 --> 01:47:43.909
...stopping the clock again
with 16 seconds left.

01:47:46.840 --> 01:47:49.229
Flip right, dive left, Indian.

01:47:49.440 --> 01:47:52.000
Now, if we don't make it,
everybody yell time.

01:47:52.200 --> 01:47:54.031
Everybody yell time.
On one. Ready?

01:47:59.760 --> 01:48:03.719
Blue 29! Blue 29!
Set!

01:48:04.720 --> 01:48:07.154
<i>Ball goes back to Crewe...</i>

01:48:10.040 --> 01:48:13.396
Time! Time!

01:48:13.760 --> 01:48:16.479
Crewe calls for his third
and last time out

01:48:16.680 --> 01:48:18.955
<i>with seven seconds left on the clock.</i>

01:48:19.600 --> 01:48:21.670
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

01:48:23.680 --> 01:48:25.432
Where the hell's he going?

01:48:26.640 --> 01:48:27.959
Let's find out.

01:48:28.840 --> 01:48:33.197
<i>Crewe has taken his last time out
and he's heading toward the bench.</i>

01:48:33.400 --> 01:48:38.315
<i>He's heading toward the bench
followed by his entire offensive unit.</i>

01:48:39.440 --> 01:48:40.759
<i>Most unusual...</i>

01:48:41.800 --> 01:48:45.156
<i>I don't know what they're doing,
it's silent as a church.</i>

01:48:46.080 --> 01:48:49.789
<i>It looks more like a prayer meeting
than a huddle.</i>

01:48:50.000 --> 01:48:52.230
<i>Whatever happens,
regardless of the outcome,</i>

01:48:52.440 --> 01:48:55.477
<i>this has been one fantastic showing.</i>

01:48:55.680 --> 01:48:58.399
We've come too far together
to stop now.

01:48:58.600 --> 01:49:01.797
For Granny, for Nate,

01:49:04.520 --> 01:49:08.274
for Caretaker, let's do it.

01:49:16.080 --> 01:49:18.389
Mean Machine!

01:49:21.240 --> 01:49:22.832
Mean Machine!

01:49:25.680 --> 01:49:28.513
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

01:49:40.440 --> 01:49:43.318
- Hold it down!
- Cool it!

01:49:44.640 --> 01:49:47.154
Set!

01:49:48.520 --> 01:49:50.431
Hut!

01:51:17.160 --> 01:51:21.551
<i>Thirty-six, thirty-five,
in favour of the Mean Machine.</i>

01:51:29.800 --> 01:51:31.074
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

01:51:31.280 --> 01:51:33.350
<i>like the fabled phoenix of old...</i>

01:51:44.840 --> 01:51:47.229
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

01:51:47.440 --> 01:51:50.830
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

01:51:51.040 --> 01:51:54.555
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

01:51:54.760 --> 01:51:56.751
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

01:52:19.920 --> 01:52:26.029
- You know, you guys ain't half bad.
- You're right.

01:52:27.680 --> 01:52:29.113
Fuck you, boy.

01:52:29.680 --> 01:52:32.114
Not today, boss.

01:52:40.040 --> 01:52:42.713
History.

01:52:42.920 --> 01:52:46.993
We stopped 'em. We are number one!

01:52:55.960 --> 01:52:59.111
Where's your goddamn
power theory now?

01:52:59.320 --> 01:53:01.231
He's trying to escape.

01:53:01.440 --> 01:53:04.079
- Oh, shit!
- Officer!

01:53:04.280 --> 01:53:06.191
- Crewe!
- I'm talking to you!

01:53:08.800 --> 01:53:10.074
Crewe!

01:53:10.280 --> 01:53:12.589
He's trying to escape. Shoot him!

01:53:13.200 --> 01:53:16.158
- Crewe!
- You going to let him escape? Shoot.

01:53:16.360 --> 01:53:19.033
- Shoot him, you... Shoot him!
- Crewe!

01:53:20.400 --> 01:53:24.473
- Crewe!
- Kill him! Kill that son of a bitch!

01:53:24.680 --> 01:53:26.272
Shoot him!

01:53:45.640 --> 01:53:47.870
Game ball.

01:54:02.200 --> 01:54:04.475
Stick this in your trophy case.

01:54:10.680 --> 01:54:13.194
I knew you could do it!
